questionListItems.title: How do i pay my rental car parking fees at barrierless hdb parking?

answer.body:
For drivers without the Parking.sg app, you can pay your parking fees using your CashCard in your vehicle IU, as you would at existing Electronic Parking System (EPS) car parks.


However, we highly recommend downloading the Parking.sg app to enjoy automatic payment of your parking fees, without having to rely on CashCard payments at the gantry. Plus, first-time downloaders get three free parking sessions!


To get started, simply download the app from the Apple Store or Google Play Store. Once downloaded, you can automatically pay your parking fees on your next visit to any of the car parks that have implemented the Parking@HDB system.

questionListItems.title: Where can I see what card Iâ€™m using

answer.body:
To check your credit card details, follow these simple steps:

  1. Tap on the Menu icon (three lines on the top left corner) in the app.

  2. Select "Remove Card". Rest assured, this will not remove your card details yet.


Use this page to see the last 4 digit of your card number. If you intend to change card, you may remove and add a different card again.

questionListItems.title: Am I entitled to a 10-minute grace period after I have parked via the app?

answer.body: No, you will need to activate your parking session immediately via the app after you have parked your vehicle. This differs from Electronic Parking System (EPS), where a 10 minutes grace period is provided for motorists to locate a parking lot after entering the car park, to do a quick drop off or pick up passengers.

questionListItems.title: Does the app track my parking history?

answer.body:
Yes, you can view your parking history in the app. Here's how:

  1. Open the app and access the left-side menu

  2. Select "History"

  3. You'll be able to see a list of your previous parking sessions

Please note that if you uninstall the app, you won't be able to view your parking history on your phone.

questionListItems.title: If I do not have any credit card, are there other alternatives?

answer.body: Yes, there are other payment methods you can use if you don't have a credit card. One option is to use a virtual credit card, such as Singtel Dash or other payment providers. Please note that we do not accept any liability for any damage through the use of virtual credit cards.

questionListItems.title: I have a Class 1 disability label. Can the app give me the first hour free?

answer.body: Yes, you can still enjoy your first hour of parking for free, which is no different from current practice. If you need to continue parking after the first hour, you will need to start a parking session using the app.

questionListItems.title: What happens if I forget to bring my phone or if I have no network coverage?

answer.body: If you are unable to park using the app for these reasons stated above, you will have to display parking coupons. Alternatively, you can consider parking your vehicle at nearby car parks that operate on the Electronic Parking System (EPS).

questionListItems.title: When must I start the parking session?

answer.body: You should start a parking session via the Parking.sg app as soon as you park in a designated parking lot. Enforcement officers are trained to identify digitally parked vehicles, so make sure to use the app.

questionListItems.title: Why am I not able to locate car parks nearby?

answer.body: To locate car parks nearby, please make sure that you have turned on the location function in your phone setting.

questionListItems.title: Why do I see parking charges on my credit card bill for days I did not use the app?

answer.body:
The reason for this is that our app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement to reduce clutter on your card statements. Parking sessions payments will be batched every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier) into bills. So, you may find that some Bill IDs contain only one session whereas some are a combination of two or more sessions.


To check your payment history, simply refer to the 'BILL' tab under the History page in the app. There, you can match the Bill IDs and their charges against the assigned Bill ID under your credit card statement. If everything matches up, then there's no need to worry! We hope that this clears up any confusion you may have had about our payment batching process.


However, if you still feel that the charges are wrong, please email feedback@parking.sg with the following details:

  1. Picture of your card statement (please exclude sensitive information)

  2. Screenshot of your history in the parking app

  3. Vehicle number

questionListItems.title: Will the app prompt me to extend the parking session nearing its expiry?

answer.body:
Yes, Parking.sg will notify you via the app 10 minutes before your parking session expires and again at the point of expiry. To receive these notifications, make sure to grant permissions to the app to push notifications to your phone and set Parking.sg to have high priority notifications in your phone settings.


To extend your session, go to the Parking.sg app and click "Extend" on your current parking session.

questionListItems.title: Why does it show that my card is expired or declined?

answer.body:
You can try removing and re-adding the card to the app, or to use a different card to see if the issue persists.

1) Tap on the Menu button on the top left corner of the app, this is shown as an icon with three lines.

2) Tap on Remove Card. Your card details will be shown as a confirmation. Tap on Remove to proceed.

3) Tap on the Menu button on the top left corner of the app again

4) Tap on Add Card and key in your card details.

5) Kindly try to book another parking session.

If the above steps did not work, kindly try closing/exiting the app fully and relaunching the app. You may need to delete and reinstall the app to restart. Please export any history if necessary.

questionListItems.title: How do I pay for whole day parking?

answer.body: You can do so by entering the full duration in the app. If the duration entered exceeds the whole day parking rate for the car park, it will be capped at the whole day rate. You may wish to refer to the physical signboard located at the car park to confirm if it support the whole day parking scheme.

questionListItems.title: I want to change my car number but I canâ€™t find the main page

answer.body: You can simply delete the existing vehicle in your app and re-enter the new vehicle information. To delete vehicle number, tap on your existing vehicle number field on the app main page, and click on the "X" beside the vehicle number you wish to delete from the list. Once you have deleted the old vehicle number, tap on the vehicle number field again and proceed to key in your new vehicle information.

questionListItems.title: Is there a deposit needed to use the app?

answer.body: No deposits are needed, just ensure you have a debit/credit card and you are able to use the app for payment.
